          "class": "top-titled",
          "summary": "This table contains three columns and fifteen rows. The first row is a header row, and it labels each column: “Exposure ( rem ),” “Health Effect,” and “Time to Onset ( without treatment ).” Under the “Exposure ( rem )” column are the following: 5 – 10, 50, 55, 70, 75, 90, 100, 400, 1000, two blank cells, 2000, and two more blank cells. Under the “Health Effect” column are the following: changes in blood chemistry, nausea, fatigue, vomiting, hair loss, diarrhea, hemorrhage, possible death, destruction of intestinal lining, internal bleeding, death, damage to central nervous system, loss of consciousness, and death. Under the “Time to Onset ( without treatment” column are the following: a blank cell, hours, two blank cells, 2 – 3 weeks, two blank cells, within 2 months, two blank cells, 1 – 2 weeks, one blank cell, minutes, and hours to days.",
